The course allows to become more aware of the basic features of academic texts and to practice reading and referencing academic texts and, more generally, academic writing skills and academic presentation.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the course is to provide an overview of the basic features of an academic text and to enable the development of reading, referencing, referencing and academic writing skills as well as presentation skills through practical tasks.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course student * knows the peculiarities of writing an academic text; * knows how to use the Institute of Education's thesis writing and formatting guide and refers correctly and according to the reference system; * can write an academic text based on both Estonian and English base texts; * knows the principles of process-oriented text creation and applies them in writing groups; * prepares a proper presentation and delivers it based on the academic style.
